-Merger-with-MPLX/</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 82\n| 2015\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Abbvie]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Pharmacyclics]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|21|2015}}\n|<ref>https://www.wsj.com/articles/abbvie-to-buy-pharmacyclics-in-21-billion-deal-1425528086</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 83\n| 2018\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Keurig Green Mountain]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Dr Pepper Snapple Group]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 21.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|21|2018}}\n|<ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/us-dr-pepper-snapp-m-a-keurig-idUSKBN1FI1II</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 84\n| 2011\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Sanofi]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Genzyme]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20.1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|20.1|2011}}\n|<ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/us-genzyme-sanofi-idUSTRE71E4XI20110216</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 85\n| 2012\n| {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Anheuser-Busch InBev]] \n| {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Grupo Modelo]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20.1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|20.1|2012}}\n|<ref>https://www.cleveland.com/business/2012/06/inbev_to_buy_out_modelo_for_20.html</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 86\n| 2016 \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Energy Transfer Partners]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Sunoco Logistics Partners]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|20|2016}}\n|<ref>https://www.cnbc.com/2016/11/21/first-trump-deal-sunoco-logistics-to-acquire-energy-transfer-partners.html</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 87\n| 2018 \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[The Blackstone Group]] \n| {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Thomson Reuters]] <small>(Financial & Risk Unit)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|20|2018}}\n|<ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/us-thomsonreuters-m-a-blackstone-idUSKCN1MB3PY</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n=== 2020s ===\nTop M&A deals worldwide by value ($20 billion or larger) from 2020 to 2029:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n!Rank\n!Year\n!Purchaser\n!Purchased\n!Transaction value<br/><small>(in billions USD) {{font color|red|(with debt)}}</small>\n!Inflation adjusted<br/><small>(in billions USD) {{font color|red|(with debt)}}</small>\n!Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| 2020\n| {{flagicon|UK}} [[Aon plc]]\n| {{flagicon|UK}} [[Willis Towers Watson]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|30.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|30|2020}}\n|<ref>https://www.wsj.com/articles/aon-to-merge-with-willis-towers-watson-in-all-stock-deal-valued-at-30-billion-11583758247</ref><ref group=\"N\">Not Completed</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==State owned enterprises==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n!Rank\n!Year\n!Purchaser\n!Purchased\n!Total asset value<br/>{{nowrap|<small>(billions USD)</small>}}\n!Inflation adjusted<br/>{{nowrap|<small>(billions USD)</small>}}\n!Note\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| 2017\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Shenhua Group]]\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China Guodian Corporation]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|278.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|278|2017}}\n| In August 2017, [[State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission of the State Council|SASAC]] announced that [[China Guodian Corporation]] (one of China's largest coal-fired power generators) and [[Shenhua Group]] (China\u2019s biggest coal miner) would be jointly restructured, with Shenhua Group becoming [[China Energy Investment Corporation]] and absorbing China Guodian Corporation to become the largest power company in the world by installed capacity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/us-china-power-shenhua-guodian-analysis-idUKKCN1B918C|title=Power of love: China's latest arranged match rattles utilities|first=Meng Meng and Josephine|last=Mason|website=reuters.com|accessdat