ing [[BASF]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chemanager-online.com/en/news-opinions/headlines/chemchina-and-sinochem-merge-2018|title=ChemChina and SinoChem to Merge in 2018 - chemanager-online.com - Chemistry and Life Science|first=Wiley-VCH Verlag GmbH & Co.|last=KGaA|website=www.chemanager-online.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201033411/http://www.chemanager-online.com/en/news-opinions/headlines/chemchina-and-sinochem-merge-2018|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/264312/chinese-firms-chemchina-and-sinochem-said-talks-over-mega|title=Chinese firms said to be in mega-merger talks. But do they have chemistry?|first=William|last=Turvill|date=8 May 2017|website=cityam.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201042029/http://www.cityam.com/264312/chinese-firms-chemchina-and-sinochem-said-talks-over-mega|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.afr.com/business/manufacturing/tieup-between-sinochem-and-chemchina-in-a-class-of-its-own-20170510-gw1gf2#|title=Tie-up between Sinochem and ChemChina in a class of its own|date=10 May 2017|website=afr.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201042048/http://www.afr.com/business/manufacturing/tieup-between-sinochem-and-chemchina-in-a-class-of-its-own-20170510-gw1gf2|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/article/chemchina-sinochem-merger-create-worlds-largest-chem-group/|title=ChemChina-Sinochem merger to create world's largest chem group|website=atimes.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119163742/http://www.atimes.com/article/chemchina-sinochem-merger-create-worlds-largest-chem-group/|archive-date=19 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2020 ChemChina and Sinochem consolidated their agricultural assets into a new holding company, to be called Syngenta Group.<ref>https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-chemchina-sinochem-syngenta/chemchina-sinochem-merge-agricultural-assets-syngenta-idUKKBN1Z40HB</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| 2015\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China Power Investment]]\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[State Nuclear Power Technology]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|112.6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|112.6|2015}}\n| In June 2015 the Chinese cabinet approved plans to merge state owned China Power Investment (CPIC) with State Nuclear Power Technology increasing the exports of nuclear technology from the country, creating the new entity [[China Power New Energy Development Company Limited]], with assets of more than $112.6 billion) and annual revenues of more than $32.6 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.power-technology.com/news/newschina-announces-merger-of-state-nuclear-power-technology-and-the-china-power-investment-4590782|title=China announces merger of State Nuclear Power Technology and the China Power Investment - Power Technology|date=1 June 2015|website=power-technology.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831001232/http://www.power-technology.com/news/newschina-announces-merger-of-state-nuclear-power-technology-and-the-china-power-investment-4590782|archive-date=31 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/C-Chinese-nuclear-giant-officially-launched-1607155.html|title=Chinese nuclear giant officially launched|website=www.world-nuclear-news.org|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701010744/http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/C-Chinese-nuclear-giant-officially-launched-1607155.html|archive-date=1 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| 2018\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China National Nuclear Corp]]\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China Nuclear Engineering & Construction ]]\n| style=\"text-align