d regulator approval issues.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.investegate.co.uk/unilever-plc--ulvr-/rns/statement-re-announcement-by-kraft-heinz-company/201702171315072133X/|title=FE Investegate -Unilever PLC Announcements - Unilever PLC: Statement re announcement by Kraft Heinz Company|access-date=2017-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219030914/http://www.investegate.co.uk/unilever-plc--ulvr-/rns/statement-re-announcement-by-kraft-heinz-company/201702171315072133X/|archive-date=2017-02-19|url-status=live}}</ref> The bid was formally dropped on February 19, citing the complexities of acquiring control in a Dutch entity without the support of shareholders.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-39022692|title=Kraft Heinz drops Unilever takeover bid|first=Howard|last=Mustoe|date=20 February 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=21 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919060637/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-39022692|archive-date=19 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| 1999\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[MCI WorldCom]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Sprint Nextel|Sprint]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|129.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|129|1999}}\n| The US [[United States Department of Justice|Department of Justice]] and [[European Commission]] prohibited the merger on competition grounds, with the DoJ filing a lawsuit against the transaction.<ref name=\"wolfstreet.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-00-668_en.htm|title=European Commission - PRESS RELEASES - Press release - Commission prohibits merger between MCI WorldCom and Sprint|access-date=2016-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923035417/http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-00-668_en.htm|archive-date=2016-09-23|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/uk/news/doj-files-to-block-worldcom-sprint-merger/|title=DOJ files to block WorldCom-Sprint merg